Hundreds of migrants from Turkey are currently moving to the Greek islands in the east of the Aegean. According to the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR), 174 people died on this route last year. Federal Minister of the Interior Horst Seehofer has now announced his intention to visit both countries.
Together with his French colleague and the responsible EU Commissioner, he wanted to find out in Turkey about " the refugee situation, " said Seehofer on Friday. Afterwards he wanted to learn out more about the " administrative problems of the Greeks " in Athens in order to be able to help deal with them.
A spokesperson for the EU Commission confirmed Seehofer's planned trip on Friday with EU Interior Commissioner Dimitris Avramopoulos and French Interior Minister Christophe Castaner.
In Greece, an unusually large number of migrants from Turkey continue to arrive. On Tuesday alone, 654 people moved to the Greek islands, according to the Greek Ministry of Civil Protection on Wednesday.
Is Turkey deal still working?
